                    <comment id="12444500" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Tue, 24 Oct 2006 21:40:02 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;It would also simplify some scorers if doc() wasn&apos;t undefined before next() or skipTo() was called, but instead -1.&lt;br/&gt;
This undefined nature of doc() often requires more state to be kept around about the scorers.&lt;br/&gt;
Things like TermScorer would just need a change from &quot;int doc&quot; to &quot;int doc=-1&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is there any scorer that this would impose a burden or cost on?&lt;br/&gt;
Thoughts?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12444506" author="paul.elschot@xs4all.nl" created="Tue, 24 Oct 2006 21:52:46 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Repeating a comment just posted at &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-693&quot; title=&quot;ConjunctionScorer - more tuneup&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-693&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;skipTo() as first call on a scorer should work. ReqExclScorer and ReqOptSumScorer depend on that for the excluded and optional scorers.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12444547" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Wed, 25 Oct 2006 00:06:20 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;DisjunctionMaxScorer turned out to be the only scorer I could see with that problem.&lt;br/&gt;
Here&apos;s the patch w/ tests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12444572" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Wed, 25 Oct 2006 05:26:58 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch committed after further tests were added.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
